          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 7.5cm*7.5cm NaI(Tl)phosphor + EMI 6711 type,",
                "10 cm cathode diameter multiplier. The detector is",
                "placed in the middle of a 1x1x1 m lead house with 10 cm",
                "thick walls.",
                "55-Cs-134-M1 residual nucleus left in its 137 keV",
                "isomeric state whose half-life is 2.895+-0.005 Hours."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The following internal conversion coefficients of the",
                "127 keV gamma line (from isomeric state) were used:",
                " .Alpha(K) = 2.6+-0.04 (Keisch,J.Inorg.Nucl.Chem.17,",
                "                                              183,1961)",
                " .Relative intensity of partial conversion coefficients",
                "    K/l/m = 23/34/6 (Caldwell,Phys.Rev.78,407(1950))",
                "The 797 keV and 802 keV gamma transitions of Ba-134",
                "were used to determine the ground state activity of",
                "Cs-134. They were found to represent respectively",
                "72.5 and 10.5% of this activity. According to",
                "Keister (Phys.Rev.97,451(1955)), Alpha(K) is less than",
                "0.003 for both transitions, thus negligible for the",
                "experiment accuracy."
              ]
            }
          ],
